Again Listers, I am begging forgiveness.  I did not read catch this fellows
questions before posting.

estimated time of events:

Thursday Evening...

Establish Camp Biffath
Someone to build a small fire
Have  a beverage and enjoy my friends (will I be the only one there?)

Friday Morning and Day

Coast the 66 down the hill and start applying new brake lines
Curse, and wait for assistance
Watch as my trusty friend fixes my ride
Direct traffic, and establish the Dixie Bus Gathering arena
Pre Cook chili meat
build a little fire
have a beverage
Enjoy the tunes provided by Mr. Gordon and Mr. Baker and others

Saturday Morning

We will cara bus early to the COVVC show
Expect to leave the camp no later than 8am
 8:45 am  Arrive at the show site and register the OVT entries

I will be leaving the show about 1 pm to head back to the camp to prepare
the chili

I have posted signs to get you back from the show, plus I have a flier with
detailed directions (provided you can read)

Saturday Evening

Eat the chili (fry the cook!!!!)
Fellowship with our fellow bus pilots
Enjoy a beverage
Enjoy the tunes of our acoustical friends

Sunday Morning

Some will want to leave early, so I want to cook breakfast EARLY, so they
can enjoy the trip home

What is early?  Depends on when the earliest plans to leave.  I suppose 7
ish will make it.



